==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{m|la|incarceratus}}, past participle of {{m|la|incarcerare||to imprison}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|in||in}} + {{m|la|carcer||a prison}}, meaning "put behind lines (bars)" – Latin root is of a lattice or grid. Related to {{m|en|cancel||cross out with lines}} and {{m|en|chancel||area behind a lattice}}.

See also {{m|en|carcerate}} and {{m|en|cancer}}.

